The paper deals with the problem of releasing protected sensitive data at a future point in time, which is a common concern in the field of computer security (cs.CR). The proposed solution involves using smart contracts in Ethereum blockchain networks, which falls under the category of distributed computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses the use of a set of peers to jointly follow the proposed timed-release service protocol, which is related to database systems (cs.DB) and cybersecurity (cs.CY). Finally, the paper involves modeling the problem as an extensive-form game with imperfect information, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG).
